"Fettweis X., van Ypersele J.-P., Gallée H., Lefebre F., Lefebvre W.","The 1979-2005 Greenland ice sheet melt extent from passive microwave data using an improved version of the melt retrieval XPGR algorithm",2007,"Geophysical Research Letters","34","5", L05502,"","",,,10.1029/2006GL028787,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34249866537&partnerID=40&md5=722affc04f539b84e6d17c148e252c3e","Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron, 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; UMR 5183, Laboratoire de Glaciologie et Géophysique de l'Environnement, Université Joseph Fourier, 54, rue Molière, F-38402 Saint-Martin d H'ères, France; Integrated Environmental Studies, Flemish Institute for Technological Research, Boeretang 200, B-2400 Mol, Belgium","Fettweis, X., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron, 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; van Ypersele, J.-P., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron, 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; Gallée, H., UMR 5183, Laboratoire de Glaciologie et Géophysique de l'Environnement, Université Joseph Fourier, 54, rue Molière, F-38402 Saint-Martin d H'ères, France; Lefebre, F., Integrated Environmental Studies, Flemish Institute for Technological Research, Boeretang 200, B-2400 Mol, Belgium; Lefebvre, W., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron, 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium","Analysis of passive microwave satellite observations over the Greenland ice sheet reveals a significant increase in surface melt over the period 1979-2005. Since 1979, the total melt area was found to have increased by +1.22 × 107 km2. An improved version of the cross-polarized gradient ratio (XPGR) technique is used to identify the melt from the brightness temperatures. The improvements in the melt retrieval XPGR algorithm as well as the surface melt acceleration are discussed with results from a coupled atmosphere-snow regional climate model. From 1979 to 2005, the ablation period has been increasing everywhere over the melt zone except in the regions where the model simulates an increased summer snowfall. Indeed, more snowfall in summer decreases the liquid water content of the snowpack, raises the albedo and therefore reduces the melt. Finally, the observed melt acceleration over the Greenland ice sheet is highly correlated with both Greenland and global warming suggesting a continuing surface melt increase in the future. Copyright 2007 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Acceleration; Global warming; Mathematical models; Melting; Moisture; Snow; Albedo; Cross-polarized gradient ratio; Melt acceleration; Snowpack; Climatology; algorithm; ice sheet; microwave imagery; remote sensing; satellite imagery; Arctic; Greenland; Greenland Ice Sheet",,,,,,"Abdalati, W., Steffen, K., Snowmelt on the Greenland ice sheet as derived from passive microwave satellite data (1997) J. Clim, 10, pp. 165-175; Abdalati, W., Steffen, K., Greenland ice sheet melt extent: 1979-1999 (2001) J. Geophys. Res, 106, pp. 33,983-33,988; Armstrong, R.L., Knowles, K.W., Brodzik, M.J., Hardman, M.A., (1994) DMSP SSM/I Pathfinder daily EASE-Grid brightness temperatures, July 1987 to December 2005, , http://nsidc.org/data/nsidc0032.html, Natl. Snow and Ice Data Cent, Boulder, Colo; Bamber, J.L., Layberry, R.L., Gogineni, S.P., A new ice thickness and bed data set for the Greenland ice sheet: 1. Measurement, data reduction, and errors (2001) J. Geophys. Res, 106, pp. 33,773-33,780; Box, J.E., Survey of Greenland instrumental temperature records: 1873-2001 (2002) Int. J. Climatol, 22, pp. 1829-1847; Chen, J.L., Wilson, C.R., Tapley, B.D., Satellite gravity measurements confirm accelerated melting of Greenland ice sheet (2006) Science, 313, pp. 1958-1960. , doi:10.1126/science.1129007; Chylek, P., Dubey, M.K., Lesins, G., Greenland warming of 1920-1930 and 1995-2005 (2006) Geophys. Res. Lett, 33, pp. L11707. , doi:10.1029/2006GL026510; De Ridder, K., Gallée, H., Land surface-induced regional climate change in southern Israel (1998) J. Appl. Meteorol, 37, pp. 1470-1485; Fettweis, X., Gallée, H., Lefebre, L., van Ypersele, J.-P., Greenland surface mass balance simulated by a regional climate model and comparison with satellite derived data in 1990-1991 (2005) Clim. Dyn, 24, pp. 623-640. , doi:10.1007/s00382-005-0010-y; Fettweis, X., Gallée, H., Lefebre, L., van Ypersele, J.-P., The 1988-2003 Greenland ice sheet melt extent by passive microwave satellite data and a regional climate model (2006) Clim. Dyn, 27, pp. 531-541. , doi:10.1007/s00382-006-0150-8; Gallée, H., Schayes, G., Development of a three-dimensional meso-γ primitive equations model (1994) Mon. Weather Rev, 122, pp. 671-685; Gallée, H., Guyomarc'h, G., Brun, E., Impact of the snow drift on the Antarctic ice sheet surface mass balance: Possible sensitivity to snow-surface properties (2001) Boundary Layer Meteorol, 99, pp. 1-19; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis. Contribution of Workings Group I to the Third Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, , Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change , edited by J. T. Houghton et al, 881 pp, Cambridge Univ. Press, New York; Johannessen, O.M., Khvorostovsky, K., Miles, M.W., Bobylev, L.P., Recent ice sheet growth in the interior of Greenland (2005) Sciencexpress, p. 510. , doi:10.1126/science.1115356; Knowles, K., E. Njoku, R. Armstrong, and M. J. Brodzik (2002), Nimbus-7 SMMR Pathfinder Daily EASE-Grid Brightness Temperatures [CD-ROM], Natl. Snow and Ice Data Cent., Boulder, ColoKrabill, W., Greenland Ice Sheet: Increased coastal thinning (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett, 31, pp. L24402. , doi:10.1029/ 2004GL021533; Luthcke, S.B., Zwally, H.J., Abdalati, W., Rowlands, D.D., Ray, R.D., Nerem, R.S